<h1 class="mylist">My lists</h1>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-4">
        <% lists.forEach(function(l) { %>
            <%= l.name %>
        <div class="cardlayout">
                <div class="cardcontent">
                    <img id="divimg"src="https://i.imgur.com/utD8k6r.jpg" alt="">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Long Island Iced Tea</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">A Long Island iced tea or Long Island ice tea is a type of alcoholic mixed drink typically made with vodka, tequila, light rum, triple sec, gin, and a splash of cola, which gives the drink the same amber hue as iced tea.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <br>
            <div class="cardlayout">
                <div class="cardcontent">
                    <img id="divimg" src="https://i.imgur.com/EJucFsZ.jpg" alt="">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Adios MF</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">The Adios Motherfucker cocktail (or the AMF drink, in mixed company), despite its vulgar name, is basically just a Long Island Iced Tea with two ingredients swapped: blue cura√ßao instead of triple sec, and a splash of lemon-lime soda instead of cola.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <br>
            <div class="cardlayout">
                <div class="cardcontent">
                    <img id="divimg" src="https://i.imgur.com/JMc7rPj.jpg" alt="">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Old Fashioned</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">The old fashioned is a cocktail made by muddling sugar with bitters and water, adding whiskey, and garnishing with orange slice or zest and a cocktail cherry. It is traditionally served in an old fashioned glass, which predated the cocktail.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <% }) %>
    </div>
</div>
